Onto budget matters now and&nbsp;chief justice Martha Koome says the judiciary must be adequately funded before the midterm review of the national budget for effective delivery of justice. Koome is warning that the independence of the judiciary will be compromised as long as it is not secured by its own independent fund.&nbsp;She says that&nbsp;underfunding of the judiciary has not only increased backlog of cases but also forced Kenyans to travel 175 kilometers to access justice. &nbsp;
